 
Switch.
With some muscle you move the switch down.
"The switch is stuck, you need someone stronger to move it."
Crates.
The crates are all empty.
Door.
You need a special key to open this door.

Light red liquid filled keg.
Your muscles expand as you take a drink.
The liquid has lost its effectiveness.
You flip the switch and hear grating off in the distance.
"A skeletal knight steps out of a forming mist and says -To let you pass I will need you to say a prayer over my bones found close by, when this is done you can pass-"
Old bones.
The bones feel incredibly cold to the touch.
You say a prayer over the bones. 
"The skeletal knight appears from the mist, nods and disappears into the mist again."
Something slimey moves behind this brick wall.
Wall with missing bricks.
You find a grey key where one of the bricks used to be.
You find a silver key where one of the bricks used to be.
Chest.
You need a key to open this chest.
"A skeletal looking cleric steps out of a quick forming mist and says - I was tortured down here long ago and my bones were scattered throughout this level, I will let you pass only when you have destroyed what remains of me and return here, you will feel which bones they are when you see them...-  He fades away."
You find and destroy one of the clerics bones. 
The cleric appears again and nods at you -Thank you I will never forget your kindness I can rest in peace at last -  He then fades away.
You get a bad feeling from the bones.
Iron Maiden
There's nothing but spikes in the Iron maiden.
You search the Burial niche and find some gold.
The bones seems to charge with electricity !!.
These are really old bones...really old.
You gain knowledge from these ancient bones.
Long dead adventurer.
You search the body and find some gold.
Button
"A mist forms and a shadowy figure of a skeletal noblemen steps in front of you saying -The undead are restless in this tomb, before I can let you leave you must visit each one of them- the noblemen shoves you back and then vanishes."
"The skeletal noblemen appears from the mist, nods his head, then vanishes."
Burial niche
Skeleton in a cage.
The skeleton grabs for you.
A strange force reaches out of the wall and grabs you.
The door will not budge.
Sack
You find some half decent food in the sack.
A scrawled message on the brick reads   2=1  3=2  1=3
